# The Wheel of Time · the loom of the Ages

The Wheel of Time turns, and Ages come and pass, leaving memories that become legend, then myth, and are long gone when the Age that gave them birth comes again. It is the great loom at the heart of the cosmology — a wheel of seven spokes, seven Ages, turning without beginning and without end. What was, will be again.

From the lives of people — the threads — the Wheel weaves the Pattern of the Ages. Each life is a thread, and the Wheel takes them all and works them into the whole, the vast unending cloth of what is and what will be. The weaving is driven by the One Power, drawn from the True Source, the force that turns the Wheel itself.

Its emergence is spiritual because the Wheel is the turning itself — the eternal return, the rebirth of Ages, the truth that memory fades to legend and legend to myth before the Age comes round once more. It is not a person to be met nor a force to be channeled, but the shape of time and the promise that the turning never ends.
